      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(logging): prune non-idle stale diagnostic session states",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen `requestStuckSessionRecovery()` fails with `status: \"failed\"`, the diagnostic session state stays non-idle forever because `recoveryOutcomeMutatesSessionState()` returns `false` and `applyRecoveryOutcomeToDiagnosticState()` returns early. The entry accumulates as a ghost in `diagnosticSessionStates` indefinitely.\n\nThis PR transitions `status: \"failed\"` recovery outcomes to idle — **only when the diagnostic state generation is still current** (no newer recovery has modified the entry). The existing stale-idle prune logic then removes them naturally. Other non-mutating outcomes (`skipped`, `already_in_flight`) and stale-generation failed outcomes are preserved.\n\nFixes #91697\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/logging/diagnostic-session-recovery-coordinator.ts`**: In `applyRecoveryOutcomeToDiagnosticState()`, when `outcome.status === \"failed\"` AND `isDiagnosticSessionStateCurrent()` confirms the generation has not changed, transition the entry to `\"idle\"` with `queueDepth = 0`. 1 file, +11 lines.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Failed stuck-session recovery leaves diagnostic entries permanently non-idle. After fix: failed + current generation → idle transition; failed + stale generation → preserved; skipped → preserved.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Node v22.22.0, Linux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64, openclaw commit 3b658bb297. tsx v4.22.3.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n1. Wrote proof script importing `diagnosticSessionStates`, `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates`, `getDiagnosticSessionState`, `peekDiagnosticSessionState`, `isDiagnosticSessionStateCurrent` and `recoveryOutcomeMutatesSessionState`\n2. Script tests 3 cases: failed+current generation, failed+stale generation, skipped noop\n3. Ran `npx tsx scripts/proof-91721-v5.mjs`\n\n**Evidence after fix (terminal capture):**\n\n```\n$ npx tsx scripts/proof-91721-v5.mjs\n\n============================================================\nrecovery-path ghost state — generation guard proof\n============================================================\nnow  = 2026-06-10T12:00:00.000Z\nTTL  = 30 minutes\n\n--- Simulating recovery outcomes ---\n\nCase 1: failed + generation current\n  gen: request=0 current=0\n  after: state=idle queueDepth=0\n\nCase 2: failed + generation STALE\n  gen: request=2 (stale) current=0 (newer recovery)\n  after: state=processing (generation guard → PRESERVED)\n\nCase 3: skipped noop\n  after: state=processing (unchanged)\n\n--- After prune ---\nentries remaining: 2 (failed-stale-gen + skipped)\n\n--- Verification ---\nfailed+current → idle                ✓\nfailed+current → pruned              ✓\nfailed+stale-gen preserved           ✓\nfailed+stale-gen still present       ✓\nskipped state preserved              ✓\n\n✓ All checks passed.\nexit code: 0\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** 3 entries → failed+current transitions to idle and is pruned. Failed+stale-gen (generation mismatch) is preserved — a newer recovery owns this entry. Skipped noop is preserved unchanged. The generation guard ensures only entries whose state has not been modified since the request was created are transitioned to idle.\n\n**What was not tested:** Full gateway restart with stuck-session recovery, heartbeat-driven stuck-session detection.",
